Sentencas: LaNi(Fe)O-3 (LNF) is one of the promising cathode materials for intermediate- temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Application of LaNi(Fe)O3 as SOFC cathode

Sentencas: However, LNF is more reactive with ZrO2-based electrolyte than conventional La(Sr)MnO3 in the sintering temperature region.
Titulo: Application of LaNi(Fe)O3 as SOFC cathode

Sentencas: In this paper, we examine the relationships among LNF sintering characteristics, reactivity, and cell performance to investigate the potential of LNF.
Titulo: Application of LaNi(Fe)O3 as SOFC cathode

Sentencas: We show that the current-voltage characteristics of cells using LNF as the cathode are drastically improved by preliminary loading at a very high current density.
Titulo: Application of LaNi(Fe)O3 as SOFC cathode

Sentencas: The cathodic overvoltage became one order of magnitude smaller after the preliminary loading, and the cells generated the maximum power density of 1.56 W/cm(2) at 800 degreesC. (C) 2004 The Electrochemical Society.
Titulo: Application of LaNi(Fe)O3 as SOFC cathode
